title: All types dialog shows obfuscated classes
description: When using JDK 1.4, the All types dialog in the application displays obfuscated classes such as 'a', 'a1', 'b', 'c', 'd', etc. These obfuscated classes should be less prominent or hidden to improve usability.
OB: The All types dialog in the application shows obfuscated classes.
EB: The obfuscated classes should be less prominent or hidden in the All types dialog.
SR:
1. Open the application.
2. Navigate to the All types dialog.
3. Observe the obfuscated classes being displayed prominently.
4. Verify that the obfuscated classes should have less prominence or be hidden.
